<TITLE> 15,000 primary teachers up for recruitment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com) -- About 15,000 primary teachers will be recruited in fiscal 2007-08 and 60 percent of them will be women, according to the proposed budget. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam in his budget speech Thursday said the government had prepared a national work plan for primary education. He said 55 lakh primary students would be given monthly stipend at the rate of Tk 100. Actions are underway to bring back dropouts in 11,000 schools. "In the next fiscal year, 10,000 teachers will be trained. As many as 18,186 classrooms will be built." As many as 6.5 lakh people from among those who have attained literacy through mass education programme will be provided with income generating training through continuous education within the next fiscal year. "Mosque and temple-based child and mass education will be strengthened," he said. bd
